I was in the King room, working the upper rim of the area.  I used my pet to attack a goblin, two more goblins joined in, and an evoker started tossing spells from across the room.  This wasn't that big of a deal for me, as I'd beaten another group that was almost exactly the same just a few minutes earlier.<br>
I probably let off one nuke, although I don't recall for certain.  What I do remember is that I was hit once with a nuke from the evoker, I decided to cast a heal on the pet, and pretty much at the same time that I started to cast the heal, all three of the meleeing goblins, which had been firmly glued to the pet, broke free and attacked me instead.  The pet followed the goblins, as when I looked back at what had happened from my bind point, I spotted at least one hit that the pet got in on the normal goblins.<br>
The heal shouldn't have increased agro because I never completed it (and from what I've heard here, renew spells don't draw agro anyway).  The evoker nuking me might have theoretically been the trigger, but I've never seen a nuke that upped the agro level toward anyone but the person who cast the nuke.<br>
Anyone know just what happened here?<br>
